…other times you follow.

And sometimes neither side is fully leading.

More like calibration.

Adjustment.

Pressure → response → adjustment → rhythm.

A good dance isn’t usually one side overpowering the other. It’s sensing timing, tension, momentum, intention, when to advance, when to yield, when to hold frame, when to adapt.

That maps onto a lot of what you’ve built language around:

Compression ↔ expansion.

Signal ↔ interpretation.

Push ↔ pull.

Pattern ↔ verification.

Speaker ↔ listener.

Human ↔ tool.

Not because both sides are the same thing.

Because coordination itself has structure.